ubuntu-game-session (0.7) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Replace the ubuntu-game-desktop session with a new ubuntu-game-launcher
    package. On a full Ubuntu system the desktop experience is now the real
    GNOME session; gamescope was never able to host GNOME, only to run nested
    per-game, so the custom labwc + waybar + wofi mini-desktop is dropped in
    favour of layering gaming tooling onto GNOME.
    - Drop deps labwc, waybar, wofi, swaybg, network-manager-gnome, fonts-noto;
      remove the labwc/waybar/wofi configs, the wofi launcher, power menu, and
      the ubuntu-game-desktop wayland session entry.
    - Depend on ubuntu-game-session (brings gamescope and installs the Steam
      snap via its postinst), gamemode, and mangohud. Replaces/Conflicts the
      old ubuntu-game-desktop package for clean upgrades.
    - Add /usr/bin/ubuntu-game-run: a composable wrapper that always applies
      GameMode and optionally MangoHud (--mangohud) and nested gamescope
      (--gamescope[=OPTS]). Recommended as a Steam per-game launch-option
      prefix: "ubuntu-game-run -- %command%". --mangohud uses the host
      "mangohud" wrapper (LD_PRELOAD), which works for native and Flatpak
      games; the host MangoHud cannot reach the confined Steam snap.
    - Add a "Steam (Gamescope)" application entry that runs the whole Steam
      client inside nested gamescope so every game inherits FSR/frame-pacing.
      MangoHud for snap games is enabled per game via Steam launch options
      ("mangohud %command%"), documented in the README, since host MangoHud
      cannot cross the snap sandbox.
  * No change to ubuntu-game-session (gamescope + Steam Big Picture kiosk) or
    ubuntu-game-handheld (autologin into Big Picture); the handheld experience
    is unaffected.

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 18:00:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.6) resolute; urgency=medium

  * ubuntu-game-desktop: improve launcher discoverability — label the waybar
    launcher button "🎮 Apps" with a filled pill style so it is clearly
    clickable; update tooltip to list all three launch methods (click, Super,
    right-click); show a one-time welcome notification on first login that
    explains how to open the launcher.
  * ubuntu-game-desktop: fix panel not appearing — pass waybar config and
    style paths explicitly in autostart instead of relying on XDG_CONFIG_DIRS
    propagation; add nm-applet and waybar output to ubuntu-game-desktop.log
    for easier debugging.
  * ubuntu-game-desktop: add libnotify-bin dependency for notify-send support.

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 16:21:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.5) resolute; urgency=medium

  * ubuntu-game-desktop: add ubuntu-game-launcher script — a wofi-based
    application launcher that automatically wraps any .desktop entry whose
    Categories field includes "Game" in `gamescope -f --`, providing frame
    timing, upscaling, and HDR for all installed games without editing any
    .desktop files. Non-game apps launch normally. Games are marked with a
    🎮 prefix in the launcher list.
  * Wire ubuntu-game-launcher into labwc keybindings (Super, Super+Space,
    right-click on desktop) and the waybar launcher button.

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 16:02:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * ubuntu-game-session: only launch Steam in Big Picture / gamepadui mode
    when GDM autologin is active for the current user; manual session
    selection now starts plain Steam.
  * Add new binary package ubuntu-game-desktop: a lightweight Wayland gaming
    desktop (labwc + waybar + wofi) where games are launched via per-game
    gamescope wrappers rather than a gamescope kiosk session. Includes a
    waybar panel with Wi-Fi status/connection editor, battery indicator, app
    launcher, clock, and power controls (logout, reboot, shut down).

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 15:33:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Rename ubuntu-game-autologin to ubuntu-game-handheld.
  * Drop HHD pip/venv/AppImage/udev installation from postinst — HHD is
    now a proper package dependency (Depends: hhd) built from the
    companion ../hhd source package.
  * Simplify ubuntu-game-handheld.postinst: only configure GDM autologin,
    polkit, sudoers, boot session reset service, and enable hhd@user.service.
  * Simplify ubuntu-game-handheld.postrm: remove udev rule and HHD symlink
    cleanup (now owned by the hhd package).
  * State directory renamed to /var/lib/ubuntu-game-handheld.
  * Revert Build-Depends to debhelper-compat + build-essential only.
  * Update standalone setup script to install hhd via apt (with pip fallback).

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 14:19:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Split single package into two binary packages:
    - ubuntu-game-session: core session (gamescope wrapper, desktop entry,
      Steam snap install); suitable for any desktop or laptop.
    - ubuntu-game-autologin: GDM autologin, HHD, boot reset service, polkit
      rule, and desktop shortcut; depends on ubuntu-game-session; intended
      for handheld gaming PCs (Legion Go, Steam Deck, etc.).
  * Switch Steam installation from Valve APT repo to Steam snap.
  * Rename source package from udeck to ubuntu-game-session.
  * State directory renamed to /var/lib/ubuntu-game-autologin.

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 14:00:00 -0400

ubuntu-game-session (0.1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Rebrand gaming session from "Steam OS" to "Ubuntu Game Session".
  * Rename binaries: steamos-session → ubuntu-game-session,
    steamos-session-select → ubuntu-game-session-select.
  * Rename session desktop file: steamos.desktop → ubuntu-game-session.desktop.
  * Rename systemd service: steamos-autologin-reset → ubuntu-game-session-autologin-reset.
  * Rename sudoers file: steamos-desktop-switch → ubuntu-game-session-switch.
  * Update XDG_SESSION_DESKTOP and XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP env vars accordingly.
  * Update all references in postinst, postrm, scripts, and README.

 -- Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>  Sat, 21 Jun 2026 13:48:00 -0400


